<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="consistency">Consistency</h3>
<p>Dialog, Alert, and other components use this for their close/remove use cases. Use it for similar use cases to preserve consistency.</p>
<m-row>
  <m-col>
    <m-alert type="success">Lorem ipsum dolor</m-alert>
  </m-col>
  <m-col>
    <m-tag>lorem <m-close></m-close></m-tag>
    <m-tag>ipsum <m-close></m-close></m-tag>
    <m-tag>dolor <m-close></m-close></m-tag>
  </m-col>
  <m-col>
    <m-dialog>Lorem ipsum dolor</m-dialog>
    <button onclick="document.querySelector('m-dialog').showModal()" ord="primary">Open Dialog</button>
  </m-col>
  <m-col>
    <img src="/m-logo.png" alt="" width="50px">
    <m-close></m-close>
  </m-col>
</m-row>
<h3 id="styling">Styling</h3>
<p>Close inherits text properties like color and font size. You can further style it with <a href="/helper-classes">helper classes</a> and custom CSS, but be careful not to change it to such a degree that it becomes unfamiliar.</p>
<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>Add <code>role="button"</code> and a helpful <code>aria-label</code>.</p>
